**Prioritizing Index Optimization**

I'm now focused on indexing. I realized that combining `where` with `orderBy` in Firestore, without a pre-existing index, can cause errors. I've decided, for this iteration, to fetch data first using the appropriate queries (e.g., using `where` for employees) and then sort the results client-side in JavaScript. This avoids forcing index creation on the user for this sample application. I'll be modifying `firestore.rules` and `pages/Concerns.tsx`. I'll also update the "Copy Rules" text in `pages/ManageUsers.tsx`.


